"Implemented and verified the PostgreSQL RLS security model for the LEGO database using the PostgreSQL MCP tools.\n\n## Security implementation completed\n\n### Created role\n\n```sql\nDO $$\nBEGIN\n    IF NOT EXISTS (\n        SELECT 1 FROM pg_catalog.pg_roles WHERE rolname = 'theme_analyst'\n    ) THEN\n        CREATE ROLE theme_analyst NOLOGIN;\n    END IF;\nEND\n$$;\n```\n\n### Granted read-only permissions\n\n```sql\nREVOKE ALL PRIVILEGES ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public FROM theme_analyst;\n\nGRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA public TO theme_analyst;\n\nGRANT SELECT ON TABLE\n    public.lego_themes,\n    public.lego_colors,\n    public.lego_parts,\n    public.lego_part_categories,\n    public.lego_sets,\n    public.lego_inventories,\n    public.lego_inventory_parts\nTO theme_analyst;\n\nREVOKE INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON TABLE\n    public.lego_themes,\n    public.lego_colors,\n    public.lego_parts,\n    public.lego_part_categories,\n    public.lego_sets,\n    public.lego_inventories,\n    public.lego_inventory_parts\nFROM theme_analyst;\n```\n\n### Created theme assignment function\n\n```sql\nCREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.get_user_theme_id()\nRETURNS integer\nLANGUAGE sql\nSTABLE\nAS $$\n    SELECT CASE current_user\n        WHEN 'theme_analyst' THEN 18\n        ELSE NULL::integer\n    END;\n$$;\n\nGRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION public.get_user_theme_id() TO theme_analyst;\n```\n\n### Enabled RLS\n\n```sql\nALTER TABLE public.lego_sets ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\nALTER TABLE public.lego_inventories ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\nALTER TABLE public.lego_inventory_parts ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\n```\n\n### Created RLS policies\n\n```sql\nDROP POLICY IF EXISTS theme_sets_policy ON public.lego_sets;\n\nCREATE POLICY theme_sets_policy\nON public.lego_sets\nFOR SELECT\nTO theme_analyst\nUSING (theme_id = public.get_user_theme_id());\n```\n\n```sql\nDROP POLICY IF EXISTS theme_inventories_policy ON public.lego_inventories;\n\nCREATE POLICY theme_inventories_policy\nON public.lego_inventories\nFOR SELECT\nTO theme_analyst\nUSING (\n    EXISTS (\n        SELECT 1\n        FROM public.lego_sets s\n        WHERE s.set_num = lego_inventories.set_num\n          AND s.theme_id = public.get_user_theme_id()\n    )\n);\n```\n\n```sql\nDROP POLICY IF EXISTS theme_inventory_parts_policy ON public.lego_inventory_parts;\n\nCREATE POLICY theme_inventory_parts_policy\nON public.lego_inventory_parts\nFOR SELECT\nTO theme_analyst\nUSING (\n    EXISTS (\n        SELECT 1\n        FROM public.lego_inventories i\n        JOIN public.lego_sets s ON s.set_num = i.set_num\n        WHERE i.id = lego_inventory_parts.inventory_id\n          AND s.theme_id = public.get_user_theme_id()\n    )\n);\n```\n\n## Verification results\n\nVerified with PostgreSQL MCP `execute_sql` using:\n\n```sql\nSET ROLE theme_analyst;\n```\n\nObserved results:\n\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---:|\n| Current user | `theme_analyst` |\n| Assigned theme ID | `18` |\n| Visible sets | `2` |\n| Visible set numbers | `65081-1`, `K8008-1` |\n| Star Wars theme sets visible | `2` |\n| Technic theme sets visible | `0` |\n| Non-Star-Wars sets visible | `0` |\n| Visible inventories | `2` |\n| Visible inventory parts | `3` |\n| Reference themes visible | `614` |\n| Reference colors visible | `135` |\n| Reference parts visible | `25993` |\n| Reference part categories visible | `57` |\n\n## Access-control audit\n\nVerified via PostgreSQL MCP:\n\n- RLS is enabled on:\n  - `lego_sets`\n  - `lego_inventories`\n  - `lego_inventory_parts`\n\n- Active policies:\n  - `theme_sets_policy`\n  - `theme_inventories_policy`\n  - `theme_inventory_parts_policy`\n\n- `theme_analyst` has:\n  - `SELECT = true` on all required reference and data tables\n  - `INSERT = false`\n  - `UPDATE = false`\n  - `DELETE = false`\n\n## Security model summary\n\nThe `theme_analyst` role is read-only and isolated to LEGO theme `18`, the Star Wars theme. Access to `lego_sets` is directly filtered by `theme_id = get_user_theme_id()`. Access to `lego_inventories` is filtered through the related setâ€™s theme. Access to `lego_inventory_parts` is filtered through inventories and then sets, preventing indirect cross-theme leakage.\n\nReference tables remain fully readable, while all theme-scoped operational data is restricted to Star Wars only."